        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-06T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="148" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d148">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/2–645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-06T16:00:00+01:00">February 6, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 6—11:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1287. Comea 174. Acting Soviet representative on EAC has informed me that his
                    Government has approved the protocol on zones of occupation in Germany and the
                    agreement on control machinery in Germany. I am informing Mr. Stettinius by
                    military channel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
